p: There was no significant difference in total lipids among the different treatments but muscle triacylglycerol was lowest with the animal by-product diet and highest with the ω3LC1.41 diet ( Table 6). Fish fed the marine and animal by-products diets showed the highest and lowest level of sterol in muscle tissues respectively ( Table 6). Diet ω3LC0 resulted in significantly higher contents of 20:4ω6 than medium marine diet. Animal by-products, ω3LC0, and ω3LC1.41 diets led to the highest DHA/EPA ratio, while the marine diet resulted in the lowest ratio ( Table 7).
